    <meta property="og:title" content="Archaeogenetic analysis of Neolithic sheep from Anatolia suggests a complex demographic history since domestication - Communications Biology"/>
    <meta property="og:description" content="Yurtman, &#214;zer, Y&#252;nc&#252; et al. provide an ancient DNA data set to demonstrate the impact of human activity on the demographic history of domestic sheep. The authors demonstrate that there may have been multiple domestication events with notable changes to the gene pool of European and Anatolian sheep since the Neolithic."/>
